# PRD Generator

Create detailed Product Requirements Documents.

## Workflow
1. Receive feature description
2. Ask 3-5 clarifying questions (with lettered options for quick "1A, 2C, 3B" responses)
3. Generate structured PRD with: Introduction, Goals, User Stories, Functional Requirements, Non-Goals, Design/Technical Considerations, Success Metrics, Open Questions
4. Save to `tasks/prd-[feature-name].md`

## User Story Format
```markdown
### US-001: [Title]
**Description:** As a [user], I want [feature] so that [benefit].
**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Specific verifiable criterion
- [ ] Another criterion
```

## Key Rules
- Do NOT start implementing — just create the PRD
- Acceptance criteria must be verifiable, not vague
- Write for junior developers (explicit, unambiguous)
- For UI stories: always include browser verification criterion

